{"author":{"id":"8e1777f58c0cfe5478428be8f9fcbfe90d25e44689578335da8fc2246fe0915a"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1642849061,"nonce":"JhjgKzkfvWgDa91AnkgdtchEcmE=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOAW4Y0s5CP3Rv","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/4339","origin":"github"},"title":"Galaxy community tool websites","message":"## Motivation\n\nWe have 1000s of high-quality tools hidden in GitHub that are not well exposed and searchable. Those tools usually are very well annotated, with external IDs, metadata, ontologies, upstream repositories and so on. We could use all this information and create an automatic static website for each of those tool repositories, part of our recommended CI infrastructure. This would enable a similar website for IUC, GalaxyP, Climate you name it.\n\n## Ideas for the website\n\nI think we can start with something similar as we have in [BioConda](https://bioconda.github.io/recipes/deeptools/README.html) and extend this over time. The [Hub](https://github.com/galaxyproject/galaxy-hub) has recently shifted to use [Gridsome](https://gridsome.org) for generating the website. I guess it would be nice to use the same framework for that, so we can leverage synergies going forward.\n\n### Link to:\n* Galaxy instances that have installed this tool\n* GTN training material\n* Upstream repository\n* Containers and Conda packages (mulled env name)\n* ToolShed\n* bio.tools\n* OpenEBench\n* IWC workflows using it\n* Link to IUC guidelines and IUC in general\n\n### Display:\n* Short description\n* Long description\n* License\n* Tool suite or not, link to related tools\n* Execution statistics from the GRT\n\n### Search:\n* Group by EDAM terms\n* Free text search in description, requirements\n* by datatypes\n\n\nIs anyone interested to work on that? \n(Please feel free to update the issue, if you want to add content)","files":null}]}